{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9c66dea0-9c9d-4175-aa7d-f5d85444c5ed","content":"The change is straightforward. In your project file, either **remove** the `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` property or set it to `false`:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Remove this line (or set to false): -->\n    <!-- <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest> -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's the only required change. `MSTest.Sdk` 3.8+ uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** by default — the `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` property was explicitly opting out of it.\n\n**Key things to be aware of after switching:**\n\n1. **CLI**: Use `dotnet test` as before, but the underlying runner changes. You can also run the test executable directly.\n2. **`--filter`** syntax remains the same.\n3. **If you use `.runsettings`**: They're still supported, but some VSTest-specific adapter settings may need adjustment.\n4. **CI/TRX output**: Add `--results-directory` and `--report-trx` if you need TRX reports (they're no longer emitted by default).\n5. **Remove** any explicit `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` package reference if present — `MSTest.Sdk` already handles it.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d8012006-2ef5-4b00-9e88-1f004cac9777","outputTokens":330,"requestId":"A02A:2C9D9E:BFE4A2:E0B2A9:69FE866B"},"id":"65be9e0e-ac8e-46fc-90f1-0a8b1e7629cc","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:57:24.728Z","parentId":"dabd06ab-2f55-479e-95ae-e9a3a7caa2e7"}
